elects the http icb nasa gov invention html Past NASA Invention of the Year winners NASA Invention of the Year Award which is supported by the ICB with technical assistance publicity and monetary awards The ICB supports the http www hq nasa gov office codea codeae Office of the Chief Engineer and the http www hq nasa gov office codeq Office of Safety and Mission Assurance who co sponsor the selection of the http icb nasa gov swy htm NASA Software of the Year Award Information about this event including the call letter is available at this http icb nasa gov swoyinfo html site Current and past NASA Software of the Year winners are referenced from http icb nasa gov nasaswy html Past NASA Software of the Year winners here From 1991 through 2002 the ICB granted 119 awards for exceptional scientific and technical contributions to NASA s mission which are archived in http icb nasa gov excp htm this place of honor One or more innovators must receive at least 5 000 for the contribution to be classified as exceptional The ICB honors contributors with initial awards whose 1 innovations have been reported in NASA Tech Briefs 350 per author 2 software has been approved for release by NASA to qualified users 1 000 for a sole author 500 each for multiple authors or 3 inventions have received approval for patent application by NASA under the Space Act 1 000 for a sole inventor 500 each for multiple inventors An individual must first report his her invention to NASA using an http invention nasa gov invention disclosure or new technology report as a first step in the process for qualifying a scientific or technical contribution for NASA adoption sponsorship support or use A http invention nasa gov website known as eNTRe has been provided for one s use to begin the task of capturing and protecting the intellectual property The ICB also acts as the approval body for grants of waiver to NASA s rights in contractor inventions Changes in the law in 1984 automatically grants waiver for sma